%N A391950 Triangle T(n,k) of coefficients of polynomials arising from Gaussian-weighted Chebyshev integrals.
%C A391950 Triangular sequence, read by rows, of coefficients of polynomials P_n(x) = Sum_{k = 0..n-1} T(n,k)*x^(2*k+1), defined by the following recursive relation: P_1(x) = 2*x; P_n(x) = 2*x^(2*n-1) - x^2*P_{n-1}(x) + 2*(2*n-1) * Sum_{j = 1..n-1} x^(2*n-2*j-2)*P_j(x).
%C A391950 These polynomials appear in the explicit expression of Gaussian-weighted integrals of Chebyshev polynomials of the first kind T_n: L^(2*n+1) * Integral_{x=-1..1} e^-(L*x)^2 * T_{2*n}(x) dx = -P_n(L)*e^(-L^2) + Q_n(L)*sqrt(Pi)*erf(L) for L>0 and n>1.
%C A391950 Polynomials Q_n seem to satisfy Q_n(x) = Sum_{k = 0..n} (-1)^k*A370706(n*(n+1)/2+n-k)*x^(2*k).
%F A391950 T(n,k) = 2*delta(n-1,k) - T(n-1,k-1) + 2*(2*n-1) * Sum_{j = 1..n-1} T(j,k-(n-j-1)), for n >= 1 and 0 <= k < n and 0 elsewhere.
%e A391950 The first rows of the triangle are:
%e A391950           x     x^3    x^5  x^7 x^9
%e A391950 P_1:      2;
%e A391950 P_2:     12;     0;
%e A391950 P_3:    120;     8;     2;
%e A391950 P_4:   1680;   160;    48;   0;
%e A391950 P_5:  30240;  3360;  1064;  24;  2;
%e A391950 ...
%t A391950 c[n_Integer?Positive, k_Integer] /; 0 <= k < n := c[n, k] = Module[{c1, c2, c3}, c1 = If[k == n - 1, 2, 0]; c2 = If[k >= 1, -c[n - 1, k - 1], 0]; c3 = 2 (2 n - 1) Sum[If[k >= n - j - 1, c[j, k - (n - j - 1)], 0], {j, 1, n - 1}]; c1 + c2 + c3]; c[_, _] := 0; Flatten[Table[c[n, k], {n, 1, 9}, {k, 0, n - 1}]]
